---
description: Database and ORM boundaries for Rust services
globs: **/*-service/**/*.rs
alwaysApply: false
---

# DB Conventions

- Use PostgreSQL + `toasty` as default persistence stack unless explicitly overridden.
- Keep all DB wiring and ORM models in `infrastructure` only.
- Map ORM models to domain entities at repository boundaries.
- Do not place ORM derives/traits in `domain` entities.
- In `Db::builder().models(...)`, register only ORM model types.
- Generate IDs/timestamps in one consistent layer (repository/adapter), not handlers.
- Keep connection/config values centralized; avoid inline literals in use-cases/handlers.
- Return persistence errors with context and preserve original cause for observability.
